---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use - UK Demographics"
  description="Terms of use, data licensing, and disclaimer for ukdemographics.co.uk."
>
  <article class="legal-page shell">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: 11 April 2026</p>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>About this site</h2>
      <p>
        ukdemographics.co.uk is an independent demographic research project by Tom Pickup. It
        presents publicly available government data with independent analysis
        and demographic projections.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or funded by any government
        body, political party, council, or campaign organisation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Data sources and licensing</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses data published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS),
        Home Office, Department for Education (DfE), NHS Digital, and other public
        bodies. This data is Crown Copyright and is used under the
        <a href="https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Government Licence v3.0</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Contains public sector information licensed under the Open Government
        Licence v3.0. Source attribution is provided throughout the site and on
        the <a href="/sources/">Sources</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Accuracy and projections</h2>
      <p>All reasonable care has been taken to ensure accuracy. However:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Demographic projections are statistical estimates, not predictions.
          They show what would happen if recent trends continued unchanged. They
          are not forecasts of what will happen.
        </li>
        <li>
          Data is sourced from official publications which may themselves contain
          errors, revisions, or methodological changes between releases.
        </li>
        <li>
          Analysis and commentary represent one interpretation of the data. Other
          reasonable interpretations may exist.
        </li>
        <li>
          Content may become outdated as new data is published. Check the data
          freshness indicators and "last updated" dates on each page.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Do not rely on this site as the sole basis for any decision. For
        authoritative data, go to the original source (ONS, Home Office, etc.)
        linked on every page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, I exclude liability for any loss
        or damage arising from your use of this site or reliance on its content,
        whether direct, indirect, or consequential. This includes but is not
        limited to loss arising from errors in data, projections, or analysis.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nothing in these terms excludes liability for death or personal injury
        caused by negligence, or for fraud.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Copyright</h2>
      <p>
        The underlying government data is Crown Copyright, used under OGL v3.0.
      </p>
      <p>
        All original analysis, commentary, visualisations, charts, code, and
        design on this site are copyright Tom Pickup 2026, unless otherwise
        stated. You may quote or reference this work with attribution.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        This site links to government publications and other external sources.
        I am not responsible for the content of external sites.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        I may update these terms. The date at the top shows when they were last changed.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .legal-page h1 {
    font-family: "Sora", sans-serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .legal-section h2 {
    font-family: "Sora", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-section ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-section li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }
  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
